            <ab>Ms. 350 (= Revāyat of Kāma Bohra): </ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent" n="NerangTransc.a" xml:id="YR0.4NerangTransc.a" xml:lang="Paz">
                <em>yaϑā. ahū. vairiiō. zaotā. frā.mē. mrūtē.</em> (Paz.) agr. zwt̰. yast. xvut̰. sāxta. bāšat̰. <em>aθārtuš </em> (Paz.) [k]arδan</ab>
            <ab class="ab_indent" n="NerangEnglish.a" xml:id="Y0.4NerangEnglish.a">"<em>yaϑā. ahū. vairiiō. zaotā. frā.mē. mrūtē.</em>If the <em>zōt</em> has prepared the <em>yast</em>, then he should make the <em>aθā. ratuš</em>."</ab> 
        </Nerangs>
        <Commentary id="ritualCommentary">
            <!-- <ab class="ab_indent">According to ms. 350, if the <em>zōt</em> has performed himself the preparatives, the <em>rāspīg</em> does not participate at all in the <em>wāz gīrišnīh.</em>. 
                In the other mss. the <em>rāspīg</em> always answer the <em>zōt</em> in both formulas (cf. Y0.3).</ab>
 -->        </Commentary>
